Install mongodb
sudo npm install mongodb-server

Setting up REACTjs Frontend:

if(!node.js === installed){
sudo apt install nodejs
}

if not installed:
npm i -g create-react-app

Creating the app:
create-react-app (app name)

npm i bootstrap

npm i react-bootstrap

plugins: 
1.Prettier
2.React snippets

npm i react-router-dom (for routes)

<BrowseRouter> около <App/> компонента

npm i joi-browser

npm i axios

if not installed (this is probably for node.js API check later):
npm i mongodb
sudo mkdir -p /data/db
sudo chown -R `id -un` /data/db
mongo db compass

JWT
npm i jsonwebtoken
npm i jwt-decode

change favicon.ico in index.html file
change name and shortname in manifest.json

import bootstrap in index.js!!!

Heroku npm install -g heroku

npm i prop-types
